1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:36,269 --> 00:01:38,150
Wang, let me know if you need anything.

3
00:01:38,749 --> 00:01:39,430
Bye.

4
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:42,309
I never get tired

5
00:01:42,309 --> 00:01:44,510
of this champagne-popping ritual.

6
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:47,990
It is quite fun.

7
00:01:47,990 --> 00:01:50,230
More than fun, it's super fun!

8
00:01:50,870 --> 00:01:52,510
What should we eat
for late-night snacks?

9
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:02,549
What are you looking at? Let me see.

10
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,549
Two people ordered a bottle of brandy?

11
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:07,350
Must be loaded.

12
00:02:08,669 --> 00:02:09,669
How rich.

13
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:14,709
The woman inside looks like
our company's internal auditor.

14
00:02:15,389 --> 00:02:17,070
Really? Let me see.

15
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:21,389
It really is her.

16
00:02:21,790 --> 00:02:22,510
I remember her.

17
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:24,109
She came during our training.

18
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,149
She seems to be a rigid person.

19
00:02:26,149 --> 00:02:27,989
I didn't expect her
to come to a nightclub.

20
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:31,910
Long, come here.

21
00:02:32,669 --> 00:02:33,190
What's up?

22
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:35,350
What did that woman say?

23
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:38,549
She asked me how many bottles of brandy
we open per day

24
00:02:38,829 --> 00:02:40,350
and per month.

25
00:02:40,669 --> 00:02:41,510
Quite nosy.

26
00:02:44,589 --> 00:02:47,269
She's here to check how many
bottles of brandy open per month?

27
00:02:47,589 --> 00:02:48,709
Why would she check that?

28
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:51,709
The company has policy.
For each store every month,

29
00:02:51,709 --> 00:02:54,024
if they open 2,000 bottles of brandy,
they get a rebate

30
00:02:54,024 --> 00:02:56,470
for three percent
of the purchase price per bottle.

31
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:58,709
Open 2,500 bottles,
then it's five percent.

32
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:00,470
I know that. So?

33
00:03:01,030 --> 00:03:06,389
Let's say the purchase price
is 1,200 yuan per bottle

34
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:08,470
with three percent rebate,

35
00:03:09,470 --> 00:03:10,470
then it'd be 36 yuan.

36
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:12,269
For 2,000 bottles, that'd be

37
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:13,750
72,000 yuan.

38
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,190
Over a year, that'd be

39
00:03:15,829 --> 00:03:17,190
close to 900,000.

40
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:19,829
One store gets a rebate
of nearly 900,000 yuan per year.

41
00:03:19,829 --> 00:03:22,230
A hundred stores would make it
to almost 100 million.

42
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:24,549
If every store falsified reports,

43
00:03:25,950 --> 00:03:27,109
the company would suffer.

44
00:03:28,109 --> 00:03:29,030
Exactly.

45
00:03:31,109 --> 00:03:32,829
But it's not our business.

46
00:03:49,589 --> 00:03:50,149
Mr. Xu.

47
00:03:52,269 --> 00:03:52,989
You are...

48
00:03:52,989 --> 00:03:54,950
Zhao Mei, a sales lady
from Huinan Group 1.

49
00:03:55,389 --> 00:03:56,829
We met at the Southern Mall

50
00:03:56,829 --> 00:03:58,589
during this year's Spring promotion.

51
00:03:59,030 --> 00:03:59,669
Any problem?

52
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,350
Are you sure?

53
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:06,470
I saw her once during my training.

54
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:07,630
I remember her.

55
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,750
I can't be mistaken.

56
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:12,989
Alright, got it.

57
00:04:14,350 --> 00:04:16,229
Anyway, how did you know I was here?

58
00:04:17,029 --> 00:04:18,870
There's a distributor conference
here today.

59
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:20,149
I bet you'd attend.

60
00:04:21,510 --> 00:04:23,229
The conference started this morning.

61
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:24,520
You've been waiting?

62
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:27,550
You're quite sharp.

63
00:04:29,190 --> 00:04:30,229
If you're available,

64
00:04:31,149 --> 00:04:32,829
want to join me at the conference?

65
00:04:34,469 --> 00:04:35,029
Thank you.

66
00:04:37,589 --> 00:04:39,149
(If I weren't this sharp,)

67
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:40,750
(could I get such an opportunity?)

68
00:04:41,269 --> 00:04:43,630
(Opportunities always favor those
who are well-prepared.)

69
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:53,469
Ms. Zhao, here to inspect?

70
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,029
Mr. Xu is in VIP Box 6.

71
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,589
She must know which box Mr. Xu is in.

72
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:00,510
Garrulous.

73
00:05:11,304 --> 00:05:15,693
=Episode 2=
(Innocent Bystander)

74
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:27,630
What's going on here?

75
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:29,430
For lease?

76
00:05:30,750 --> 00:05:33,190
Shut down. The owner absconded.

77
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,269
No wonder we're besties.

78
00:05:36,389 --> 00:05:37,550
Misfortune befalls us both.

79
00:05:38,269 --> 00:05:40,229
I didn't come for one week,

80
00:05:40,229 --> 00:05:42,029
and they just shut down?

81
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:43,870
I couldn't even get my payment back.

82
00:05:44,389 --> 00:05:45,430
Oh my!

83
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,550
Wasn't it fine last time I came?

84
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:48,269
Let's go.

85
00:05:48,269 --> 00:05:49,870
How could it just shut down like this?

86
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:51,990
Due to stagnant market, miss.

87
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:52,870
So what do we do?

88
00:05:53,349 --> 00:05:54,589
Read the gossip accounts?

89
00:05:54,589 --> 00:05:56,589
They're all talking about
Xu's sexual harassment.

90
00:05:58,550 --> 00:06:00,136
The company's criticized by the public.

91
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:05,389
I didn't expect Xu,

92
00:06:05,589 --> 00:06:06,589
such a seasoned player,

93
00:06:06,589 --> 00:06:08,149
would fall down over such things.

94
00:06:08,589 --> 00:06:09,909
Sexual harassment?

95
00:06:12,389 --> 00:06:13,750
Unbelievable!

96
00:06:14,149 --> 00:06:16,149
I was worried this would happen.

97
00:06:16,149 --> 00:06:19,269
So after taking over the Promotions
Department, I added two rules.

98
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:20,950
No drinking during work hours.

99
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:22,469
No unauthorized absence from post.

100
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:25,029
I hoped it would offer some protection.

101
00:06:25,389 --> 00:06:27,269
Yet what I feared most still came true.

102
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:30,029
This whole thing is really annoying,

103
00:06:30,909 --> 00:06:32,670
but I think it's a good thing for you.

104
00:06:34,909 --> 00:06:36,870
You've been
in the deputy director post for long.

105
00:06:37,229 --> 00:06:40,110
It's about time you get promoted.

106
00:06:41,229 --> 00:06:42,110
Forget it.

107
00:06:43,269 --> 00:06:46,709
Just keeping my job this time
is already a blessing.

108
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:48,709
I think you're capable.

109
00:06:49,029 --> 00:06:49,909
Don't brush this off.

110
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:50,950
Think over it carefully.

111
00:06:51,789 --> 00:06:53,149
Thank you for cheering me up.

112
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,789
Let's figure out how to take the fall.

113
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,670
Barry, I'll introduce.

114
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:12,630
It's ancient-style braised abalones.

115
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:14,510
First, simmer them slowly
in premium broth,

116
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:15,990
then gently stewed over low heat.

117
00:07:15,990 --> 00:07:16,990
A signature dish.

118
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:18,269
Give it a try.

119
00:07:18,269 --> 00:07:18,870
Okay.

120
00:07:19,309 --> 00:07:22,870
(Barry, General Manager
of GST Liquor China)

121
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,190
Mr. Li, you're quite decent.

122
00:07:24,909 --> 00:07:26,589
Our company has such a scandal,

123
00:07:26,909 --> 00:07:28,029
and it's trending online.

124
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:31,029
My phone has been ringing all day.

125
00:07:31,097 --> 00:07:31,510
(Peter Du, Sales VP of GST Liquor China)

126
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:32,149
But you?

127
00:07:32,229 --> 00:07:33,070
So far,

128
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:34,229
silent about it.

129
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,750
If you don't mention it,

130
00:07:37,589 --> 00:07:38,870
how could I possibly mention?

131
00:07:40,110 --> 00:07:41,110
But honestly,

132
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:44,950
seeing the news did make me uneasy.

133
00:07:47,269 --> 00:07:48,510
Before I give you the proposal,

134
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,190
and you're already firing people?

135
00:07:50,709 --> 00:07:53,269
Darn it! This is completely a mess!

136
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:55,469
She called me early this morning.

137
00:07:55,469 --> 00:07:56,349
Not that early.

138
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:57,550
Very early.

139
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,589
It was only 8 AM!

140
00:07:58,750 --> 00:07:59,630
9:15 AM.

141
00:08:01,149 --> 00:08:03,430
Whatever. Anyway, I was so drunk.

142
00:08:03,909 --> 00:08:07,029
And then she goes,
Xu Yuntian harassed a girl,

143
00:08:07,389 --> 00:08:09,789
one of our sales ladies, sexually.

144
00:08:09,950 --> 00:08:10,950
And then I go,

145
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,709
a scum like Xu Yuntian,

146
00:08:14,269 --> 00:08:17,110
doesn't he do this all the time?

147
00:08:18,349 --> 00:08:19,870
It's not worth waking me up.

148
00:08:20,550 --> 00:08:23,029
Then she said,
"This time it's different."

149
00:08:23,149 --> 00:08:24,630
It's a whole mess out there.

150
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,088
It's on Weibo.

151
00:08:26,152 --> 00:08:27,750
Everybody's talking about this.

152
00:08:27,909 --> 00:08:30,510
And it's going to affect
the reputation of our company.

153
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:32,270
So I said,

154
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:36,270
"Why not just fire that scum?"

155
00:08:37,070 --> 00:08:40,390
This is the most cost-effective method
among all the ways to optimize

156
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:41,608
the organizational structure.

157
00:08:42,229 --> 00:08:42,829
Hopefully.

158
00:08:44,229 --> 00:08:46,509
Mr. Li, we approached Ruijin
for cooperation this time

159
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:49,224
because of your expertise
in optimizing organizational structure

160
00:08:49,469 --> 00:08:52,670
and your extensive experience
in formulating talent strategies.

161
00:08:53,288 --> 00:08:55,270
Between cost reduction
and efficiency improvement,

162
00:08:55,270 --> 00:08:56,989
efficiency improvement is what matters.

163
00:08:58,469 --> 00:09:03,270
Especially the development
of our entire sales team.

164
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:05,989
Rest assured.
We will deliver excellent service.

165
00:09:15,869 --> 00:09:17,829
Xu Yuntian is already useless.

166
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:21,629
Do you have any candidates in mind
for his successor?

167
00:09:24,509 --> 00:09:25,070
Not yet.

168
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:28,190
This happened too suddenly.

169
00:09:29,229 --> 00:09:32,190
We'd like to hear your opinion.

170
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:38,109
It's the third quarter.

171
00:09:38,248 --> 00:09:39,509
The fourth quarter is coming.

172
00:09:39,509 --> 00:09:40,829
I've reviewed the sales data

173
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:42,910
and it's still way from the targets.

174
00:09:43,509 --> 00:09:46,469
Hiring a sales director externally now

175
00:09:46,629 --> 00:09:48,509
would require a long adjustment period,

176
00:09:48,749 --> 00:09:51,349
which would
significantly hurt the performance.

177
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:55,310
Therefore, I suggest
promoting someone internally.

178
00:09:55,869 --> 00:09:58,109
That's the safest approach right now.

179
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,829
We also prefer internal promotion.

180
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:04,150
What about
our two current deputy sales directors?

181
00:10:04,749 --> 00:10:06,910
Like Dong Yue,
he has the best performance.

182
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:08,229
And Tang Lide.

183
00:10:08,589 --> 00:10:09,950
We have three deputy directors.

184
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:12,349
You mean Zhao Mei?

185
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:15,749
She is also a deputy sales director,

186
00:10:15,749 --> 00:10:17,390
but she's in charge of promotions.

187
00:10:18,509 --> 00:10:19,150
Who is Zhao Mei?

188
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:22,030
Our commercial assistant director
in trade marketing.

189
00:10:22,950 --> 00:10:23,829
I remember her.

190
00:10:24,910 --> 00:10:26,790
She's the ex-girlfriend of Xu Yuntian.

191
00:10:27,629 --> 00:10:28,629
She is Mr. Li's wife.

192
00:10:29,589 --> 00:10:30,150
What?

193
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:32,648
Yep.

194
00:10:34,349 --> 00:10:34,869
Really?

195
00:10:36,109 --> 00:10:38,070
Yes, Zhao Mei is my wife.

196
00:10:38,229 --> 00:10:39,509
What a surprise!

197
00:10:53,910 --> 00:10:55,989
The company wants me
to attend a session tomorrow.

198
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:57,709
What kind of session?

199
00:10:59,509 --> 00:11:02,950
To state the ins and outs
of the whole matter.

200
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:07,349
About how Xu Yuntian
harassed that sales lady,

201
00:11:07,349 --> 00:11:08,709
why that sales lady was fired,

202
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,509
how this matter got leaked,

203
00:11:10,509 --> 00:11:11,910
and how this crisis escalated.

204
00:11:12,808 --> 00:11:15,349
What's most infuriating
is that many people were there that day.

205
00:11:15,349 --> 00:11:16,910
Why only me had to go to the session?

206
00:11:17,190 --> 00:11:18,310
It's not a session,

207
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:19,469
clearly a scapegoat session.

208
00:11:20,070 --> 00:11:21,390
That Qi Youlan,

209
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:23,229
the head of HR,

210
00:11:23,509 --> 00:11:25,150
is such a smooth talker.

211
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:26,749
So, Mr. Li.

212
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:29,910
Regarding the selection
of the new sales director,

213
00:11:30,349 --> 00:11:32,310
I hope you won't have personal bias.

214
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:34,469
I got that.

215
00:11:34,709 --> 00:11:36,190
You were hinting at me.

216
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,709
Know what she said about me?

217
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:41,150
She said you lack foresight

218
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:44,030
and didn't consider all potential risks.

219
00:11:44,749 --> 00:11:46,270
But if this outcome hadn't happened,

220
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:49,070
could it be said I stopped Xu Yuntian
from making further mistakes

221
00:11:49,190 --> 00:11:50,349
and I turned the tide?

222
00:11:51,229 --> 00:11:52,950
The sales director position is crucial.

223
00:11:53,430 --> 00:11:55,709
We need to select based on capability.

224
00:11:56,509 --> 00:11:59,589
Zhao Mei has led
promotional teams of hundreds

225
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:01,469
with rich management experience.

226
00:12:01,869 --> 00:12:03,430
But she's never directly done sales.

227
00:12:03,709 --> 00:12:05,790
That is indeed a major weakness for her.

228
00:12:09,989 --> 00:12:11,629
When I went to see her today,

229
00:12:12,310 --> 00:12:14,229
I saw Dong Yue coming out of her office.

230
00:12:14,270 --> 00:12:15,790
One of the deputy sales directors.

231
00:12:16,349 --> 00:12:17,509
He was there that day too.

232
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:19,624
Why didn't Qi Youlan
ask him to the session?

233
00:12:19,950 --> 00:12:22,109
Maybe he's the one
who suggested Qi Youlan

234
00:12:22,109 --> 00:12:23,190
to make you the scapegoat.

235
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:24,589
Definitely.

236
00:12:25,190 --> 00:12:26,349
When I was there,

237
00:12:26,349 --> 00:12:29,310
Qi Youlan's laughing and chatting
with Dong Yue.

238
00:12:29,509 --> 00:12:31,829
Once she saw me,
her face instantly changed.

239
00:12:32,229 --> 00:12:34,950
The kind that would put
Snow White's stepmother to shame.

240
00:12:36,136 --> 00:12:37,869
Alright. Calm down.

241
00:12:40,829 --> 00:12:42,749
I need to make my body
produce more dopamine

242
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:43,950
to cheer me up.

243
00:12:44,349 --> 00:12:45,032
I'll go run.

244
00:12:51,430 --> 00:12:52,424
Careful.

245
00:13:17,109 --> 00:13:18,670
I know another way

246
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:20,910
to produce dopamine.

247
00:13:25,469 --> 00:13:27,469
Not in the mood.

248
00:13:29,430 --> 00:13:30,390
Understood.

249
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:32,390
After this scapegoat session,

250
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:35,150
all the blame will be on me.

251
00:13:36,349 --> 00:13:38,829
My team and I
will shoulder all the blame.

252
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:41,430
And the company

253
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:44,070
can ask me to leave.

254
00:13:45,829 --> 00:13:47,670
What should I do?

255
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:52,390
Today I reached out to a headhunter,

256
00:13:53,709 --> 00:13:55,190
asking him to keep an eye out

257
00:13:55,190 --> 00:13:56,950
for any good positions.

258
00:13:56,950 --> 00:13:59,749
But I doubt there's any recently.

259
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:04,589
If I become a housewife,

260
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:06,030
you have to support me.

261
00:14:07,709 --> 00:14:08,749
I won't complain.

262
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:14,509
Actually, I thought of a way

263
00:14:15,030 --> 00:14:16,430
to keep you from getting fired.

264
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:18,910
What is it?

265
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:20,150
Three words.

266
00:14:20,829 --> 00:14:21,709
To talk about it.

267
00:14:23,190 --> 00:14:24,229
To talk about it?

268
00:14:24,349 --> 00:14:25,070
What do you mean?

269
00:14:25,469 --> 00:14:27,349
When I had dinner with your head today,

270
00:14:27,749 --> 00:14:29,749
I gathered from our conversation

271
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:32,070
your company plans
to promote someone internally

272
00:14:32,070 --> 00:14:32,989
to replace Xu Yuntian.

273
00:14:35,349 --> 00:14:37,670
You want me

274
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:39,589
to apply for the sales director position

275
00:14:40,109 --> 00:14:41,829
as Xu Yuntian's successor?

276
00:14:44,190 --> 00:14:46,270
To talk about it...

277
00:14:47,349 --> 00:14:49,430
On the surface,
it's about seeking a promotion.

278
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,030
But actually, it's to tell everyone

279
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:53,190
that regarding
the sexual harassment matter,

280
00:14:53,190 --> 00:14:54,150
I am not guilty at all.

281
00:14:54,349 --> 00:14:55,109
Exactly.

282
00:14:58,349 --> 00:15:00,950
I bet those higher-ups will think

283
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:02,829
I've lost my mind once they hear it.

284
00:15:03,469 --> 00:15:04,749
I'm in the sales department,

285
00:15:04,749 --> 00:15:06,109
but I manage promotions.

286
00:15:06,469 --> 00:15:07,950
I've never done any sales.

287
00:15:07,950 --> 00:15:09,749
Now I suddenly want
to be sales director?

288
00:15:10,229 --> 00:15:10,950
That's insane!

289
00:15:11,229 --> 00:15:12,430
It isn't the goal.

290
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:15,670
The goal is to take the initiative.

291
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:17,589
Only then can you

292
00:15:17,829 --> 00:15:19,509
get an opportunity to stay.

293
00:15:20,550 --> 00:15:21,390
For you,

294
00:15:22,109 --> 00:15:23,190
staying

295
00:15:23,869 --> 00:15:25,390
is more important than winning.

296
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:29,310
Then I need to make a big splash.

297
00:15:29,509 --> 00:15:30,509
Make a really big splash.

298
00:15:30,989 --> 00:15:32,270
Make it a grand spectacle.

299
00:15:32,430 --> 00:15:33,670
Make everyone know.

300
00:15:34,229 --> 00:15:35,550
Let everyone know

301
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:38,390
you want to be the sales director.

302
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:40,670
I need to think of a way.

303
00:15:43,749 --> 00:15:47,509
Maybe I can start
by tomorrow's scapegoat session.

304
00:15:55,709 --> 00:15:58,030
Sir, where's No. 27?

305
00:15:58,589 --> 00:16:01,109
(Actually, I thought of a way.)

306
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:03,829
But it's not quite decent.

307
00:16:11,469 --> 00:16:11,989
Move!

308
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:18,270
(In such a critical moment,)

309
00:16:19,190 --> 00:16:20,869
stop hesitating.

310
00:16:21,509 --> 00:16:22,430
At a time like this,

311
00:16:23,509 --> 00:16:24,829
save yourself first.

312
00:16:52,749 --> 00:16:55,390
The problem
is that Zeng Zixuan worked for us.

313
00:16:55,829 --> 00:16:57,829
If Zeng Zixuan weren't our sales lady,

314
00:16:58,070 --> 00:16:59,790
but just anyone from the nightclub,

315
00:17:00,168 --> 00:17:01,416
it'd have nothing to do with

316
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:03,080
workplace sexual harassment or bullying.

317
00:17:03,229 --> 00:17:04,110
We can be out of this.

318
00:17:04,134 --> 00:17:04,749
(Deng Ken, PR Director
of GST Liquor China)

319
00:17:04,749 --> 00:17:06,309
Weren't you there?

320
00:17:07,269 --> 00:17:09,029
How did Zeng Zixuan end up at the booth?

321
00:17:09,749 --> 00:17:11,509
Shouldn't she be at her post?

322
00:17:12,709 --> 00:17:13,190
Ms. Zhao.

323
00:17:13,190 --> 00:17:14,150
(That night,)

324
00:17:14,509 --> 00:17:16,910
(Zeng Zixuan wasn't
supposed to be on duty.)

325
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:18,190
I'm Zeng Zixuan,

326
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:19,430
covering for Wang Liping.

327
00:17:19,430 --> 00:17:20,309
She took a leave.

328
00:17:20,830 --> 00:17:21,390
Thanks.

329
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:26,110
I haven't seen this girl.

330
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,029
She used to work at daytime.

331
00:17:28,350 --> 00:17:29,469
Daytime?

332
00:17:29,469 --> 00:17:30,709
Can she handle it?

333
00:17:30,910 --> 00:17:31,789
I can.

334
00:17:35,110 --> 00:17:36,350
Ms. Zhao, I can do it.

335
00:17:36,630 --> 00:17:37,709
I didn't work at nighttime,

336
00:17:37,709 --> 00:17:38,789
but I know what to do.

337
00:17:39,029 --> 00:17:39,789
Ms. Zhao, trust me.

338
00:17:39,789 --> 00:17:40,910
I can definitely handle it.

339
00:17:42,989 --> 00:17:43,509
Get to work.

340
00:17:44,350 --> 00:17:45,190
I'll go then.

341
00:17:47,269 --> 00:17:49,269
(It's good for young people
to be ambitious.)

342
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,950
(We should give them opportunities.)

343
00:17:53,190 --> 00:17:54,110
(But I never expected)

344
00:17:54,590 --> 00:17:56,390
(she's way too ambitious)

345
00:17:56,390 --> 00:17:58,150
(and went to toast Xu.)

346
00:17:59,309 --> 00:18:00,749
(Then that incident happened.)

347
00:18:02,184 --> 00:18:03,749
- My subordinate!
- (I was furious.)

348
00:18:04,269 --> 00:18:06,509
- (I immediately rushed to stop Mr. Xu.)
- Sir, stay sober.

349
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:09,709
Stop it, okay?

350
00:18:09,709 --> 00:18:10,709
It's not your business.

351
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:12,029
If she can't, you do it.

352
00:18:12,029 --> 00:18:13,509
- (To protect Zeng Zixuan,)
- Sober up!

353
00:18:13,749 --> 00:18:16,390
- (I even splashed Xu with ice water.)
- Clam down.

354
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:18,509
(Dong Yue, Tang Lide,
and Liang Danning were there.)

355
00:18:18,509 --> 00:18:19,590
(They all witnessed it.)

356
00:18:21,709 --> 00:18:22,989
So, you're saying

357
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:25,309
the sales lady violated
the company policy first?

358
00:18:26,029 --> 00:18:28,190
Yes, so I fired her.

359
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:31,709
Zhao Mei fired Zeng Zixuan on the spot,

360
00:18:32,390 --> 00:18:34,069
and Zeng Zixuan held a grudge.

361
00:18:34,069 --> 00:18:37,229
That's why she leaked the video
to get back at the company.

362
00:18:37,229 --> 00:18:38,549
She got fired by Zhao Mei.

363
00:18:38,549 --> 00:18:39,590
She must be resentful,

364
00:18:40,029 --> 00:18:41,069
so wanted to escalate it

365
00:18:41,670 --> 00:18:42,630
to vent her anger

366
00:18:42,870 --> 00:18:44,590
and extort benefits from the company.

367
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:46,309
If Zeng Zixuan hadn't been fired,

368
00:18:46,309 --> 00:18:48,190
this wouldn't have happened.

369
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:49,350
So the biggest mistake

370
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:50,590
is Zhao Mei's mishandling.

371
00:18:51,269 --> 00:18:53,749
Zeng Zixuan left her post
without permission to toast.

372
00:18:53,749 --> 00:18:55,709
That's a serious policy violation.

373
00:18:56,229 --> 00:18:58,630
Sales ladies are hired and fired

374
00:18:58,630 --> 00:19:00,269
through online procedures.

375
00:19:00,509 --> 00:19:01,789
They never come to the office.

376
00:19:02,110 --> 00:19:04,789
Besides, Zeng Zixuan
admitted her mistake.

377
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:06,989
I fired her per company policy.

378
00:19:06,989 --> 00:19:09,350
I see nothing wrong
with how I handled it.

379
00:19:09,509 --> 00:19:10,590
Nothing wrong?

380
00:19:11,229 --> 00:19:14,229
No one proves if Zeng Zixuan
admitted her mistake.

381
00:19:14,830 --> 00:19:16,670
The rumor spreading online is

382
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:18,229
her being sexually harassed

383
00:19:18,229 --> 00:19:19,469
and getting fired.

384
00:19:21,069 --> 00:19:22,670
What if I can prove?

385
00:19:26,069 --> 00:19:26,870
I have evidence

386
00:19:27,670 --> 00:19:28,989
to show netizens

387
00:19:30,469 --> 00:19:31,350
that the company

388
00:19:33,069 --> 00:19:33,910
and I are innocent.

389
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:36,870
Get to the point.

390
00:19:37,469 --> 00:19:39,910
I want to make a deal with you.

391
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:45,509
Ms. Zhao, I'm sorry.

392
00:19:46,269 --> 00:19:46,910
For what?

393
00:19:48,309 --> 00:19:51,229
The company has rules for sales ladies.
No unauthorized absence from post.

394
00:19:51,229 --> 00:19:52,870
No drinking during work hours.

395
00:19:53,269 --> 00:19:54,910
So you remember these two rules.

396
00:19:55,910 --> 00:19:56,870
What's your name?

397
00:19:58,789 --> 00:19:59,469
Zeng Zixuan.

398
00:20:00,029 --> 00:20:01,269
Since you know you were wrong,

399
00:20:01,390 --> 00:20:03,950
you know what consequence you'd face.

400
00:20:05,749 --> 00:20:06,789
I'm sorry, Ms. Zhao.

401
00:20:06,910 --> 00:20:08,549
Could you give me another chance?

402
00:20:09,469 --> 00:20:11,910
Ask your supervisor to settle your pay.

403
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:13,870
With this recording,

404
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:17,229
netizens won't criticize
the company anymore.

405
00:20:18,789 --> 00:20:20,749
Zeng Zixuan is quite calm now.

406
00:20:21,269 --> 00:20:22,549
Once the news broke online,

407
00:20:22,549 --> 00:20:24,309
I had her supervisor comfort her.

408
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:28,830
She's never made
any public statements online,

409
00:20:29,190 --> 00:20:30,069
and she never will.

410
00:20:30,269 --> 00:20:31,309
Send me the recording now.

411
00:20:31,549 --> 00:20:32,590
I need to release it now.

412
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:35,190
I can send it to you,

413
00:20:37,029 --> 00:20:38,350
but you have to promise me

414
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:40,309
to guarantee Zeng Zixuan's privacy,

415
00:20:41,469 --> 00:20:44,269
and stop this matter
from escalation any further.

416
00:20:51,789 --> 00:20:52,789
(The crisis is lifted.)

417
00:20:55,950 --> 00:20:56,469
Zhao Mei.

418
00:21:01,709 --> 00:21:02,269
Ms. Qi.

419
00:21:03,910 --> 00:21:04,749
Well done.

420
00:21:06,910 --> 00:21:07,950
I'm just curious

421
00:21:08,630 --> 00:21:10,830
why you didn't mention
you had a recording yesterday.

422
00:21:12,749 --> 00:21:14,190
I forgot it at the time.

423
00:21:14,549 --> 00:21:16,069
It only hit me last night.

424
00:21:18,549 --> 00:21:19,830
Do you often record things?

425
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:23,229
It depends.

426
00:21:23,709 --> 00:21:25,989
Like when it involves resignations

427
00:21:25,989 --> 00:21:27,989
or sensitive topics,

428
00:21:28,150 --> 00:21:29,309
I just record them.

429
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:30,789
As you know,

430
00:21:31,069 --> 00:21:34,309
the situations we sales ladies face
can get quite complicated.

431
00:21:34,789 --> 00:21:35,509
Good habit.

432
00:21:37,670 --> 00:21:38,509
Take care, Ms. Qi.

433
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:42,630
(Really think I'm a pushover?)

434
00:21:44,989 --> 00:21:45,709
Get to the point.

435
00:21:46,029 --> 00:21:48,549
I want to make a deal with you.

436
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:49,509
A deal?

437
00:21:50,069 --> 00:21:51,549
Do you want to return to GST?

438
00:21:54,309 --> 00:21:55,549
Would the company let me back?

439
00:21:55,789 --> 00:21:56,830
Not at the moment,

440
00:21:57,789 --> 00:21:58,749
but I can help.

441
00:21:59,229 --> 00:22:00,350
I wouldn't go back.

442
00:22:00,989 --> 00:22:03,229
GST isn't the only company in the world.

443
00:22:04,430 --> 00:22:06,150
So you plan to look for another job?

444
00:22:07,469 --> 00:22:08,509
Already looking for it?

445
00:22:11,029 --> 00:22:11,720
No.

446
00:22:13,150 --> 00:22:14,590
But even if I can't find a job,

447
00:22:14,590 --> 00:22:16,469
I still wouldn't go back to GST.

448
00:22:16,989 --> 00:22:18,190
If I went back there,

449
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:19,390
what would others think of me?

450
00:22:21,870 --> 00:22:23,029
I understand that.

451
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:25,350
It's rare for a victim

452
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:27,269
to willingly return
to the scene of the crime.

453
00:22:30,749 --> 00:22:32,549
But if you truly care

454
00:22:32,549 --> 00:22:33,749
about what others think,

455
00:22:34,309 --> 00:22:36,069
then you really should go back to GST.

456
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:37,950
Why?

457
00:22:39,269 --> 00:22:41,469
With your current level of visibility,

458
00:22:41,910 --> 00:22:43,549
if you go work anywhere else,

459
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:46,549
this incident will keep haunting you.

460
00:22:46,549 --> 00:22:48,749
People will bring up the past, saying,

461
00:22:48,989 --> 00:22:50,269
"Look, that girl"

462
00:22:50,469 --> 00:22:52,830
"is the GST sales lady
who was sexually harassed."

463
00:22:55,069 --> 00:22:57,110
If I go back to GST,
people won't gossip about it?

464
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:58,024
Exactly.

465
00:22:58,509 --> 00:23:00,150
Because Xu Yuntian got fired,

466
00:23:00,150 --> 00:23:02,830
while you are the one being hired back.

467
00:23:02,950 --> 00:23:05,670
That shows he was the one at fault.

468
00:23:06,989 --> 00:23:07,709
Put it this way.

469
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:10,509
If you work for
any company other than GST,

470
00:23:10,509 --> 00:23:12,390
you will be a victim
of sexual harassment

471
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:13,590
and questioned by people.

472
00:23:13,590 --> 00:23:14,950
But if you return to GST,

473
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:16,910
then you will be a victor.

474
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:19,269
Facts speak louder than words.

475
00:23:26,630 --> 00:23:27,269
No rush.

476
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:29,150
Think my proposal over

477
00:23:30,269 --> 00:23:31,630
and give me your answer later.

478
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:35,190
I accept now.

479
00:23:38,789 --> 00:23:39,709
What should I do?

480
00:23:41,509 --> 00:23:43,110
Do you remember that night at Cocoon,

481
00:23:43,110 --> 00:23:45,150
the last conversation between us?

482
00:23:46,950 --> 00:23:48,430
I need you to record it again.

483
00:24:05,749 --> 00:24:07,509
(Why are so many people following up?)

484
00:24:08,549 --> 00:24:10,029
(Is our company that famous?)

485
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:13,150
(Don't these people
have anything better to do?)

486
00:24:14,509 --> 00:24:16,269
(They don't care
about floods, droughts,)

487
00:24:16,269 --> 00:24:16,910
(or wars,)

488
00:24:16,910 --> 00:24:17,989
(but focus on a girl?)

489
00:24:19,590 --> 00:24:20,590
(What moral police!)

490
00:24:21,229 --> 00:24:21,789
(Insane!)

491
00:24:25,029 --> 00:24:26,910
Zixuan, are you okay?

492
00:24:42,504 --> 00:24:43,110
Take it off.

493
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,029
Stop this.

494
00:24:46,870 --> 00:24:47,390
Take it off.

495
00:24:48,870 --> 00:24:49,670
Stop this.

496
00:24:49,670 --> 00:24:50,830
I'm not in the mood now.

497
00:24:52,150 --> 00:24:52,950
Not in the mood?

498
00:24:53,430 --> 00:24:54,430
Then what do you want?

499
00:24:55,670 --> 00:24:56,549
I don't want to talk.

500
00:24:56,549 --> 00:24:57,749
Just leave me alone.

501
00:24:58,229 --> 00:24:59,269
Want me to leave?

502
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:01,229
You can drink with the bosses

503
00:25:01,549 --> 00:25:02,989
and throw yourself at the bosses.

504
00:25:03,390 --> 00:25:04,630
But I can't even touch you?

505
00:25:05,110 --> 00:25:05,989
Stop the nonsense.

506
00:25:05,989 --> 00:25:07,269
I am just so tired.

507
00:25:07,670 --> 00:25:08,910
Tired from drinking?

508
00:25:09,229 --> 00:25:10,630
Or from keeping men company?

509
00:25:11,390 --> 00:25:12,190
Don't be ungrateful.

510
00:25:12,590 --> 00:25:13,469
I want it today.

511
00:25:13,469 --> 00:25:14,150
I want it.

512
00:25:16,069 --> 00:25:17,229
Be good.

513
00:25:19,989 --> 00:25:20,989
- Take it off.
- Don't.

514
00:25:22,509 --> 00:25:23,150
I want it today.

515
00:25:26,269 --> 00:25:26,989
What do you want?

516
00:25:27,549 --> 00:25:28,069
Let go!

517
00:25:28,509 --> 00:25:29,192
Let go!

518
00:25:30,110 --> 00:25:30,789
Let go of me!

519
00:25:30,789 --> 00:25:31,592
What do you want?

520
00:25:33,269 --> 00:25:34,509
Get off!

521
00:25:34,509 --> 00:25:35,150
Zeng Zixuan.

522
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:36,590
Don't come any closer!

523
00:25:37,630 --> 00:25:39,430
Take one more step and I'll kill you!

524
00:26:06,536 --> 00:26:08,744
David, it's me.

525
00:26:09,989 --> 00:26:12,390
You've probably seen
the news of our company.

526
00:26:14,110 --> 00:26:14,670
Right.

527
00:26:15,029 --> 00:26:17,469
Well, yesterday we posted
an audio recording online.

528
00:26:17,469 --> 00:26:18,749
I just checked the comments,

529
00:26:18,749 --> 00:26:19,989
which are really nasty.

530
00:26:19,989 --> 00:26:20,989
They're all one-sided.

531
00:26:21,229 --> 00:26:22,190
I think trolls did it.

532
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:25,989
Yes.

533
00:26:26,989 --> 00:26:29,630
So, I want you to help me look into it.

534
00:26:31,350 --> 00:26:31,976
Ms. Zhao.

535
00:26:32,749 --> 00:26:34,184
Zeng Zixuan posted this on Moments.

536
00:26:36,110 --> 00:26:37,749
(Say goodbye to this world.)

537
00:26:37,749 --> 00:26:39,150
(Forgive me for leaving.)

538
00:26:39,910 --> 00:26:40,670
(Too tired)

539
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:42,430
- (to breathe.)
- Find her now.

540
00:26:42,549 --> 00:26:44,269
Get all our sales ladies to find her.

541
00:26:44,269 --> 00:26:44,989
Okay.

542
00:26:44,989 --> 00:26:45,960
I'll go to her place.

543
00:26:54,029 --> 00:26:55,870
Stop knocking!

544
00:26:58,390 --> 00:26:59,110
Coming!

545
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:02,280
Where's Zeng Zixuan?

546
00:27:03,709 --> 00:27:04,509
It's you.

547
00:27:05,309 --> 00:27:05,910
You know me?

548
00:27:06,430 --> 00:27:07,670
You fired her.

549
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:09,670
Where did she go?

550
00:27:10,350 --> 00:27:10,952
I don't know.

551
00:27:11,269 --> 00:27:12,309
We had a huge fight,

552
00:27:12,830 --> 00:27:14,029
then I went out drinking.

553
00:27:14,229 --> 00:27:15,630
When I got back, she was gone.

554
00:27:15,630 --> 00:27:16,709
No idea when she left.

555
00:27:16,830 --> 00:27:18,056
Why don't you look for her?

556
00:27:18,509 --> 00:27:19,110
What?

557
00:27:19,910 --> 00:27:21,069
Where to?

558
00:27:21,870 --> 00:27:22,984
Zeng Zixuan isn't home.

559
00:27:23,509 --> 00:27:24,989
She's so stubborn.

560
00:27:25,509 --> 00:27:26,789
I've told her many times

561
00:27:26,910 --> 00:27:29,350
not to work as a sales lady in a bar.

562
00:27:29,630 --> 00:27:31,509
Being a waitress
in a restaurant is better.

563
00:27:31,509 --> 00:27:33,229
But she insists on working
at messy places.

564
00:27:34,509 --> 00:27:35,350
She never listens.

565
00:27:35,789 --> 00:27:37,269
She's got high ambitions

566
00:27:37,469 --> 00:27:38,728
and wants to find a rich man.

567
00:27:39,309 --> 00:27:40,509
This time it's just toasting.

568
00:27:40,549 --> 00:27:42,989
Next time, she might do something dirty.

569
00:27:42,989 --> 00:27:43,989
You're the dirty one!

570
00:27:44,989 --> 00:27:47,870
She is missing, yet you don't
look for her and talk nonsense here.

571
00:27:49,430 --> 00:27:50,350
Scum!

572
00:27:53,269 --> 00:27:54,350
Why are you cursing at me?

573
00:27:55,910 --> 00:27:57,309
You caused all this for her.

574
00:27:57,590 --> 00:27:58,870
Thank you, Mr. Wang.

575
00:27:58,870 --> 00:28:00,269
Not reaching her
might not be bad news.

576
00:28:00,269 --> 00:28:01,029
Right.

577
00:28:01,269 --> 00:28:02,830
No news is good news.

578
00:28:03,150 --> 00:28:03,789
Right.

579
00:28:03,989 --> 00:28:05,749
Please keep an eye out for me.

580
00:28:05,789 --> 00:28:08,029
- I'll inform you of any updates.
- Okay, thanks.

581
00:28:08,029 --> 00:28:08,749
Okay.

582
00:28:10,630 --> 00:28:12,229
(Would she really do something foolish?)

583
00:28:13,469 --> 00:28:14,309
(It's not worth it.)

584
00:28:15,944 --> 00:28:17,350
- Hello.
- Ms. Zhao.

585
00:28:17,350 --> 00:28:18,549
Any updates?

586
00:28:18,709 --> 00:28:19,870
Still no contact so far.

587
00:28:19,870 --> 00:28:21,670
I've asked other colleagues to help.

588
00:28:23,269 --> 00:28:25,590
Any of our sales ladies
in Zeng Zixuan's hometown?

589
00:28:26,029 --> 00:28:27,749
Ask them to go check her place.

590
00:28:28,549 --> 00:28:29,390
Mind your words.

591
00:28:29,469 --> 00:28:30,549
Don't scare her parents.

592
00:28:30,549 --> 00:28:31,430
Got it.

593
00:28:32,269 --> 00:28:32,789
Bye.

594
00:28:41,032 --> 00:28:41,989
Hello, Wang Liping.

595
00:28:42,824 --> 00:28:44,950
Hello, Ms. Zhao. I found Zeng Zixuan.

596
00:28:47,029 --> 00:28:47,749
Great!

597
00:28:49,069 --> 00:28:49,830
I'm on my way.

598
00:28:50,150 --> 00:28:50,830
Okay, bye.

599
00:28:51,190 --> 00:28:53,910
I saw people in the group are looking
for Zeng Zixuan, so I called her.

600
00:28:53,910 --> 00:28:54,910
Her phone was off.

601
00:28:54,910 --> 00:28:55,830
Then I messaged her.

602
00:28:56,150 --> 00:28:57,590
I never expected her to reply.

603
00:28:57,590 --> 00:29:00,110
She said she would come to me.
Then I called you immediately.

604
00:29:01,469 --> 00:29:02,789
I was trying to persuade her.

605
00:29:02,870 --> 00:29:04,830
I told her Ms. Zhao wouldn't hurt her.

606
00:29:05,150 --> 00:29:07,110
I can only hide thanks to her help.

607
00:29:08,029 --> 00:29:10,110
I saw she was quite calm,

608
00:29:10,910 --> 00:29:12,110
and would stay for dinner.

609
00:29:12,456 --> 00:29:12,989
This way.

610
00:29:13,749 --> 00:29:15,469
Zixuan, look who's here.

611
00:29:17,630 --> 00:29:18,390
Zixuan's gone.

612
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:20,469
Find her!

613
00:29:23,469 --> 00:29:24,110
Zixuan.

614
00:29:25,789 --> 00:29:26,469
Zixuan!

615
00:29:29,150 --> 00:29:29,749
How's it going?

616
00:29:29,989 --> 00:29:31,350
Ms. Zhao, I didn't see her.

617
00:29:32,029 --> 00:29:33,269
Then, go check over there.

618
00:29:33,269 --> 00:29:33,992
Okay.

619
00:29:36,150 --> 00:29:36,789
Zixuan!

620
00:29:43,269 --> 00:29:44,150
Zixuan.

621
00:29:57,910 --> 00:29:58,549
No, don't.

622
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:00,110
Don't jump.

623
00:30:00,870 --> 00:30:01,709
Don't jump.

624
00:30:04,789 --> 00:30:05,390
Zixuan!

625
00:30:06,590 --> 00:30:08,390
Zixuan, don't act rashly!

626
00:30:09,029 --> 00:30:09,989
Don't act rashly!

627
00:30:10,509 --> 00:30:12,430
Tell me what's on your mind.

628
00:30:12,670 --> 00:30:13,870
We can talk things over.

629
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:14,789
Come down.

630
00:30:15,870 --> 00:30:17,069
You pushed me to this.

631
00:30:18,190 --> 00:30:20,150
All of you pushed me.

632
00:30:20,910 --> 00:30:22,749
I saw those comments online.

633
00:30:22,749 --> 00:30:24,590
They're worse than we anticipated.

634
00:30:25,269 --> 00:30:27,069
I know you're upset.

635
00:30:27,670 --> 00:30:29,110
But since we had a problem,

636
00:30:29,110 --> 00:30:30,709
we just find a way to solve it.

637
00:30:30,830 --> 00:30:31,910
I promised you

638
00:30:31,910 --> 00:30:33,430
to help you get back on your feet.

639
00:30:33,430 --> 00:30:35,029
You said you would trust me.

640
00:30:35,390 --> 00:30:37,190
We've already taken the first step.

641
00:30:37,350 --> 00:30:39,509
What now? You want to quit halfway?

642
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:41,989
The first step?

643
00:30:43,150 --> 00:30:44,830
You took the first step.

644
00:30:46,190 --> 00:30:47,749
I was so stupid.

645
00:30:47,749 --> 00:30:49,989
I even believed you'd help me.

646
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:52,670
I did want to help you!

647
00:30:52,749 --> 00:30:53,448
No!

648
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:55,670
You just wanted to save
the company's reputation.

649
00:30:56,309 --> 00:30:57,870
You tricked me into
making that recording,

650
00:30:57,870 --> 00:30:59,549
making me admit I was at fault.

651
00:30:59,789 --> 00:31:01,269
Then you put my recording online,

652
00:31:01,269 --> 00:31:02,630
letting netizens cyberbully me.

653
00:31:02,630 --> 00:31:04,509
You dumped all the blame on me,

654
00:31:04,509 --> 00:31:06,789
so all of you could clear your name!

655
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:13,870
This is my fault.

656
00:31:14,110 --> 00:31:15,390
Of course, it's your fault!

657
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:17,910
They're all blaming me.

658
00:31:18,390 --> 00:31:19,989
They're all cursing me.

659
00:31:20,469 --> 00:31:22,269
So is my boyfriend.

660
00:31:22,269 --> 00:31:24,269
Everyone is cursing me!

661
00:31:24,630 --> 00:31:25,350
Right.

662
00:31:27,630 --> 00:31:29,590
I did go to toast.

663
00:31:30,110 --> 00:31:32,269
I did so just to impress the boss.

664
00:31:32,269 --> 00:31:33,630
What's wrong about that?

665
00:31:33,630 --> 00:31:35,190
- Everyone wants to climb the ladder.
- Calm down.

666
00:31:35,190 --> 00:31:35,910
Don't you want so?

667
00:31:35,910 --> 00:31:37,989
Don't all of you want
to climb the ladder?

668
00:31:37,989 --> 00:31:39,749
Why are you guys cursing me?

669
00:31:41,069 --> 00:31:43,469
Zixuan, we all want to climb the ladder.

670
00:31:43,630 --> 00:31:44,870
All of us want it!

671
00:31:46,390 --> 00:31:47,670
What if I told you

672
00:31:48,229 --> 00:31:49,590
those online comments

673
00:31:50,069 --> 00:31:51,910
were deliberately spread by someone?

674
00:31:55,749 --> 00:31:56,488
What?

675
00:31:57,190 --> 00:31:58,590
Someone hired trolls

676
00:31:59,029 --> 00:32:00,709
to deliberately smear you.

677
00:32:02,110 --> 00:32:03,029
How do you know?

678
00:32:03,029 --> 00:32:04,950
I checked the accounts cursing you.

679
00:32:04,989 --> 00:32:07,029
Besides ads, they have no real content.

680
00:32:07,029 --> 00:32:09,390
They're classic troll accounts.

681
00:32:09,749 --> 00:32:12,190
Someone is deliberately
sabotaging you behind your back.

682
00:32:12,630 --> 00:32:13,430
Not us.

683
00:32:14,069 --> 00:32:16,350
We desperately want this to blow over

684
00:32:16,350 --> 00:32:17,870
and never pour oil on the flames.

685
00:32:17,870 --> 00:32:18,989
Then who is it?

686
00:32:18,989 --> 00:32:19,509
I don't know.

687
00:32:19,509 --> 00:32:20,069
Who is it?

688
00:32:20,069 --> 00:32:21,069
I don't know.

689
00:32:24,309 --> 00:32:25,630
I was wrong, Zixuan.

690
00:32:27,269 --> 00:32:29,430
Please give me a chance
to make it right.

691
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:31,469
All I want to say now is,

692
00:32:31,469 --> 00:32:32,670
if you jumped off now,

693
00:32:32,670 --> 00:32:33,896
then only they would be happy,

694
00:32:33,989 --> 00:32:35,509
and you'd fall into their trap.

695
00:32:45,709 --> 00:32:46,269
Zixuan,

696
00:32:47,469 --> 00:32:50,269
don't you want to expose them with me?

697
00:33:11,269 --> 00:33:13,150
(The moment I hugged Zeng Zixuan,)

698
00:33:13,830 --> 00:33:15,950
(I felt like I was completely drained.)

699
00:33:17,029 --> 00:33:19,269
(When I handed the recording
over to the company,)

700
00:33:19,709 --> 00:33:22,390
(I knew this would happen.)

701
00:33:22,670 --> 00:33:24,390
(And it would definitely
harm Zeng Zixuan.)

702
00:33:25,190 --> 00:33:27,430
(But I had no choice.
I had to save myself.)

703
00:33:28,269 --> 00:33:30,390
(I needed to use Zeng Zixuan
to clear my name.)

704
00:33:31,390 --> 00:33:32,630
(But I never expected)

705
00:33:33,989 --> 00:33:36,309
(that things would escalate
to this point.)

706
00:33:41,190 --> 00:33:42,509
If you didn't go,

707
00:33:42,509 --> 00:33:43,430
she'd jump?

708
00:33:43,749 --> 00:33:44,328
Exactly.

709
00:33:48,350 --> 00:33:50,989
Would she do something irrational again?

710
00:33:53,309 --> 00:33:55,269
That's exactly what I'm worried about.

711
00:33:57,269 --> 00:33:58,390
So I was thinking,

712
00:33:59,229 --> 00:34:01,229
why don't we hire Zeng Zixuan back?

713
00:34:05,150 --> 00:34:07,910
Look, Mr. Xu has already been suspended.

714
00:34:08,430 --> 00:34:10,270
If we hire Zeng Zixuan back,

715
00:34:11,230 --> 00:34:13,549
it will prove the company
has recognized its mistake.

716
00:34:15,989 --> 00:34:17,669
Xu Yuntian's suspension

717
00:34:17,669 --> 00:34:20,350
and hiring Zeng Zixuan back
are two separate matters.

718
00:34:21,870 --> 00:34:24,870
You mentioned the company
has recognized its mistake.

719
00:34:27,270 --> 00:34:29,230
I don't quite like that phrasing.

720
00:34:30,149 --> 00:34:31,368
How can the company be wrong?

721
00:34:32,669 --> 00:34:33,830
A company is an institution.

722
00:34:34,270 --> 00:34:35,669
It can't make mistakes.

723
00:34:36,029 --> 00:34:37,469
Only individuals can make mistakes.

724
00:34:39,910 --> 00:34:40,509
I understand.

725
00:34:41,109 --> 00:34:42,230
You're stalling for time.

726
00:34:43,870 --> 00:34:45,989
I'm also worried that Zeng Zixuan

727
00:34:47,109 --> 00:34:48,790
would cause any more trouble.

728
00:34:49,669 --> 00:34:51,270
I understand the situation now.

729
00:34:51,270 --> 00:34:52,469
Let's discuss this later.

730
00:34:52,750 --> 00:34:53,509
You may leave.

731
00:34:55,950 --> 00:34:56,549
Ms. Qi.

732
00:34:57,750 --> 00:34:58,910
One more thing,

733
00:35:00,390 --> 00:35:03,069
As you can see, the work pressure
right now is quite intense.

734
00:35:03,390 --> 00:35:06,230
Many people are experiencing
psychological issues to some degree,

735
00:35:06,629 --> 00:35:08,069
especially those in low-level posts.

736
00:35:08,509 --> 00:35:09,750
Like sales ladies.

737
00:35:14,230 --> 00:35:15,189
Indeed, it's a problem.

738
00:35:16,189 --> 00:35:17,549
We should discuss this properly.

739
00:35:18,629 --> 00:35:20,910
How about we contact

740
00:35:21,710 --> 00:35:23,430
a psychological counselor?

741
00:35:24,069 --> 00:35:25,790
Have employees attend regular sessions.

742
00:35:27,549 --> 00:35:29,549
That might not target the root cause.

743
00:35:31,189 --> 00:35:32,830
Don't even think about a pay raise.

744
00:35:33,430 --> 00:35:35,430
I mean promotion opportunities.

745
00:35:35,910 --> 00:35:38,390
Even they try hard,
they can only be team leaders at best.

746
00:35:38,870 --> 00:35:41,710
The chance of promotion
to supervisors is very slim.

747
00:35:45,270 --> 00:35:46,390
I know what you mean.

748
00:35:48,270 --> 00:35:50,469
But this is a major issue,

749
00:35:51,069 --> 00:35:52,710
not something simple.

750
00:35:52,790 --> 00:35:53,790
It can't be solved soon.

751
00:35:55,189 --> 00:35:58,430
So, let's put this aside for now.

752
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:01,430
Look, the year-end is approaching.

753
00:36:01,629 --> 00:36:02,989
I've lost my Sales Director.

754
00:36:03,549 --> 00:36:06,589
And the company is under
intense public scrutiny every day.

755
00:36:06,589 --> 00:36:08,629
Berry keeps piling tasks on me.

756
00:36:13,589 --> 00:36:15,830
You have an interview tomorrow.

757
00:36:16,149 --> 00:36:16,870
That's it.

758
00:36:17,189 --> 00:36:18,029
Go rest well.

759
00:36:28,549 --> 00:36:29,069
Ms. Qi.

760
00:36:30,149 --> 00:36:31,139
Actually,

761
00:36:32,232 --> 00:36:34,109
I'm capable of being the Sales Director.

762
00:36:49,723 --> 00:36:54,463
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

763
00:36:58,913 --> 00:37:00,833
♪Too much of shame♪

764
00:37:01,179 --> 00:37:03,975
♪To waste it crying♪

765
00:37:06,433 --> 00:37:08,353
♪Leave all behind you♪

766
00:37:08,353 --> 00:37:10,633
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

767
00:37:10,753 --> 00:37:12,982
♪You know how far you've gone♪

768
00:37:13,117 --> 00:37:15,393
♪In the fire you rise again♪

769
00:37:15,579 --> 00:37:17,939
♪You made it through the worst♪

770
00:37:18,077 --> 00:37:20,281
♪The best is yet to come♪

771
00:37:20,524 --> 00:37:22,664
♪The best is yet to come♪

772
00:37:25,366 --> 00:37:26,689
♪Isn't it magical♪

773
00:37:26,689 --> 00:37:28,321
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

774
00:37:28,353 --> 00:37:30,820
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

775
00:37:30,820 --> 00:37:33,273
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

776
00:37:33,354 --> 00:37:36,002
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

777
00:37:36,091 --> 00:37:38,622
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

778
00:37:38,702 --> 00:37:40,924
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

779
00:37:41,066 --> 00:37:42,147
♪But I don't want to♪

780
00:37:42,256 --> 00:37:44,522
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

781
00:37:44,638 --> 00:37:45,703
♪Until 3 AM♪

782
00:37:45,874 --> 00:37:47,079
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

783
00:37:47,233 --> 00:37:48,466
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

784
00:37:48,557 --> 00:37:50,921
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

785
00:37:51,068 --> 00:37:55,478
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

786
00:38:10,203 --> 00:38:11,639
♪Leave all behind you♪

787
00:38:11,743 --> 00:38:14,230
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

788
00:38:14,413 --> 00:38:16,542
♪You know how far you've gone♪

789
00:38:16,729 --> 00:38:19,069
♪In the fire you rise again♪

790
00:38:19,137 --> 00:38:21,403
♪You made it through the worst♪

791
00:38:21,763 --> 00:38:23,841
♪The best is yet to come♪

792
00:38:24,090 --> 00:38:26,260
♪The best is yet to come♪

793
00:38:28,961 --> 00:38:30,113
♪Isn't it magical♪

794
00:38:30,113 --> 00:38:33,759
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

795
00:38:33,793 --> 00:38:35,649
♪And I see them sparkling♪

796
00:38:35,873 --> 00:38:38,004
♪Nobody knows♪

797
00:38:38,625 --> 00:38:40,535
♪What tomorrow brings♪

798
00:38:40,801 --> 00:38:43,124
♪You made it through the worst♪

799
00:38:43,311 --> 00:38:45,519
♪The best is yet to come♪

800
00:38:45,806 --> 00:38:47,955
♪The best is yet to come♪

801
00:38:48,251 --> 00:38:49,665
♪Isn't it magical♪

802
00:38:49,665 --> 00:38:51,877
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

803
00:38:51,951 --> 00:38:54,305
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

804
00:38:54,305 --> 00:38:55,393
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

805
00:38:55,393 --> 00:38:58,844
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

806
00:38:59,297 --> 00:39:01,571
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

807
00:39:01,985 --> 00:39:02,849
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

808
00:39:02,849 --> 00:39:04,369
♪Isn't it magical♪
